calculateMaxSwapAmountIn(address).details: The max amount of native assets the contract will swap with the user is governed by the `maxNativeSwapAmount` state variable.

returns.maxAllowed: The maximum number of tokens the user is allowed to swap for native assets.

params.toNativeAmount: Quantity of tokens to be converted to native assets.

returns.nativeAmount: The exchange rate between native assets and the `toNativeAmount` of transferred tokens.

params.decimals: Token decimals of token being transferred.
params.targetChainId: Wormhole chain ID of the target blockchain.

cancelOwnershipTransferRequest(uint16).details: Sets the pending owner state variable to the zero address.

completeTransferWithRelay(bytes).details: reverts if: - the transferred token is not accepted by this contract - the transffered token is not attested on this blockchain's Token Bridge contract - the emitter of the transfer message is not registered with this contract - the relayer fails to provide enough native assets to faciliate a native swap - the recipient attempts to swap native assets when performing a self redemption

confirmOwnershipTransferRequest().details: It checks that the caller is the pendingOwner to validate the wallet address. It updates the owner state variable with the pendingOwner state variable.

decodeTransferWithRelay(bytes).details: reverts if: - the first byte (payloadId) does not equal 1 - the length of the payload has an unexpected length

deregisterToken(uint16,address).details: The `removeAcceptedToken` function will revert if the token is not registered.

returns.localAddress: Address of the encoded (bytes32 format) token address on this chain.

params.chainId_: Wormhole chain ID of the foreign contract.
params.contractAddress: Address of the foreign contract in bytes32 format (zero-left-padded address).

params.paused: If true, requests for token transfers will be blocked and no VAAs will be generated.

params.amount: Quantity of tokens to be transferred.
params.targetChain: Wormhole chain ID of the target blockchain.
params.targetRecipient: User's wallet address on the target blockchain in bytes32 format (zero-left-padded).
params.toNativeTokenAmount: Amount of tokens to swap into native assets on the target chain.
params.token: ERC20 token address to transfer cross chain.

returns.messageSequence: Wormhole sequence for emitted TransferTokensWithRelay message.

params.token: Address of the token to update the max native swap amount for.

updateRelayerFee(uint16,uint256).details: The relayerFee is scaled by the relayerFeePrecision. For example, if the relayerFee is $15 and the relayerFeePrecision is 1000000, the relayerFee should be set to 15000000.

params.amount: Amount of USD to pay the relayer upon redemption.

updateSwapRate(uint16,(address,uint256)[.details: The swapRate is the conversion rate using asset prices denominated in USD multiplied by the swapRatePrecision. For example, if the conversion rate is $15 and the swapRatePrecision is 1000000, the swapRate should be set to 15000000. NOTE: This function does NOT check if a token is specified twice. It is up to the owner to correctly construct the `SwapRateUpdate` struct.

params.swapRateUpdate: Array of structs with token -> swap rate pairs.

updateUnwrapWethFlag(uint16,bool).details: This variable should only be set to true for chains that support a WETH contract. Some chains (e.g. Celo, Karura, Acala) do not support a WETH contract, and the address is set as a placeholder for the native asset address for swapRate lookups.

params.unwrapWeth_: Boolean that determines if WETH is unwrapped when transferred back to its native blockchain.

params.targetChain: Wormhole chain ID of the target blockchain.
params.targetRecipient: User's wallet address on the target blockchain in bytes32 format (zero-left-padded).
params.toNativeTokenAmount: Amount of tokens to swap into native assets on the target chain.

returns.messageSequence: Wormhole sequence for emitted TransferTokensWithRelay message.

calculateMaxSwapAmountIn(address).notice: Calculates the max amount of tokens the user can convert to native assets on this chain.

calculateNativeSwapAmountOut(address,uin.notice: Calculates the amount of native assets that a user will receive when swapping transferred tokens for native assets.

calculateRelayerFee(uint16,address,uint8.notice: Converts the USD denominated relayer fee into the specified token denomination.

completeTransferWithRelay(bytes).notice: Calls Wormhole's Token Bridge contract to complete token transfers. Takes custody of the wrapped (or released) tokens and sends the tokens to the target recipient. It pays the fee recipient in the minted token denomination. If requested by the user, it will perform a swap with the off-chain relayer to provide the user with native assets. If the `token` being transferred is WETH, the contract will unwrap native assets and send the transferred amount to the recipient and pay the fee recipient in native assets.

confirmOwnershipTransferRequest().notice: Finalizes the ownership transfer to the pending owner.

deregisterToken(uint16,address).notice: Deregister tokens accepted by this contract.

encodeTransferWithRelay((uint8,uint256,u.notice: Encodes the TransferWithRelay struct into bytes.

fetchLocalAddressFromTransferMessage(byt.notice: Parses the encoded address and chainId from a `TransferWithPayload` message. Finds the address of the wrapped token contract if the token is not native to this chain.

registerContract(uint16,bytes32).notice: Registers foreign Token Bridge Relayer contracts.

registerToken(uint16,address).notice: Register tokens accepted by this contract.

setPauseForTransfers(uint16,bool).notice: Sets the pause state of the relayer. If paused, token transfer requests are blocked. In flight transfers, i.e. those that have a VAA emitted, can still be processed if paused.

submitOwnershipTransferRequest(uint16,ad.notice: Starts the ownership transfer process of the contracts. It saves an address in the pending owner state variable.

transferTokensWithRelay(address,uint256,.notice: Calls Wormhole's Token Bridge contract to emit a contract-controlled transfer. The transfer message includes an arbitrary payload with instructions for how to handle relayer payments on the target contract and the quantity of tokens to convert into native assets for the user.

updateFeeRecipient(uint16,address).notice: Updates the `feeRecipient` state variable. This method can only be executed by the owner.

updateMaxNativeSwapAmount(uint16,address.notice: Updates the max amount of native assets the contract will pay to the target recipient.

updateOwnerAssistant(uint16,address).notice: Updates the `ownerAssistant` state variable. This method can only be executed by the owner.

updateRelayerFee(uint16,uint256).notice: Updates the fee for relaying transfers to foreign contracts.

updateRelayerFeePrecision(uint16,uint256.notice: Updates the precision of the relayer fee.

updateSwapRate(uint16,(address,uint256)[.notice: Updates the swap rates for a batch of tokens.

updateSwapRatePrecision(uint16,uint256).notice: Updates the precision of the swap rate.

wrapAndTransferEthWithRelay(uint256,uint.notice: Wraps Ether and calls Wormhole's Token Bridge contract to emit a contract-controlled transfer. The transfer message includes an arbitrary payload with instructions for how to handle relayer payments on the target contract and the quantity of tokens to convert into native assets for the user.
